parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Rod Bearing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rod bearings can cause the engine to seize, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine makes a loud knocking or grinding noise
the engine stalls or loses power
the check engine light may or may not be illuminated
metal flakes or debris are found in the oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Head Gasket or Head Bolt Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket or head bolts can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the check engine light may or may not be illuminated
the engine makes a loud knocking or grinding noise

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Oil Consumption or Internal Oil Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption or internal oil leak can cause the engine to fail, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the engine makes a loud knocking or grinding noise
the check engine light may or may not be illuminated

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Clutch or Hydraulic System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch or hydraulic system can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The paint delamination and peeling can lead to rust and corrosion, compromising the structural integrity of the vehicle and potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: often starting on the roof frame
and spreading to other areas; large chunks of paint coming off; rust spots appearing where the paint has peeled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door handle can cause difficulties in opening the door, potentially leading to safety issues, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: making it difficult or impossible to open the door; door handle falling off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The paint delamination/peeling can lead to rusting, which can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, and also affect the vehicle's appearance and resale value.
symptoms: especially on vehicles with Snow White Pearl color.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure/stalling can cause accidents, especially when the vehicle stalls while driving, and can also leave the driver stranded.
The electrical issues can cause safety risks, such as loss of headlights, and can also lead to accidents.
The door issues can cause safety risks, such as doors opening while driving, and can also lead to accidents.
symptoms: inability to open doors from the outside
and child safety lock engaging unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The water leaks can cause safety risks, such as electrical shorts, and can also lead to mold and mildew growth.
symptoms: Water leaks inside the vehicle cabin
especially on the front passenger and driver sides.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ignition issues can cause safety risks, such as theft, and can also lead to accidents.
symptoms: Lack of immobilizer on the ignition
allowing vehicles to be stolen with a USB.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dim headlights can cause reduced visibility while driving at night, increasing the risk of accidents and posing a safety hazard to the driver and other road users.
symptoms: making it difficult to see the road and obstacles at night
or using high beams. The low beam headlights are particularly affected
with some owners reporting that they can only see 10-20 feet in front of the vehicle.
